Authentication protocol
Kerberos, ntlm, ldap

4624 is an event ID of kerberos
Kerberos authentication---this is used to verify identity of a user or a host
It is very secure and uses symmetric keys to send the user credentials over the wire
Its provide single sign on where user doesn't have to enter the credential multiple times to access the resource in the network
It is more efficient where the application server doesn't required to validate the user credential by contacting the DC. Instead the server can authenticate the user by examining credential

3 phases of kerberos

1 AS_REQ-authentication request
   AS_REP- authentication response (this happened when logon on machine)
2 TGS_REQ-Ticket granting service request
    TGS_REP- Ticket granting service response
3 AP_REQ- application request
  AP_REP- Application response
